text:
1. Technical interns sourced for the JITCO STTP shall be coursed through JITCO-accredited supervising organizations.
2. Compliance with existing POEA rules on registration/accreditation of principals is required.
3. The following documents, duly examined and recommended for approval by the Philippine Overseas Labor Office (POLO), shall be submitted to POEA by the POEA-licensed recruitment agency for registration of the principal:
  3.1 Business registration based on Japan's Employment Security Act;
  3.2 Recruitment agency credentials;
  3.3 Technical intern offer from the principal together with list of direct intern offers;
  3.4 Technical intern employment contract between the intern and the principal.
4. Additional technical intern offers shall be approved upon presentation of:
  4.1 Request for additional technical intern from the POEA-licensed recruitment agency;
  4.2 Technical intern offer.
5. Validity of Registration:
  - Registration of the principal is valid for a maximum of four (4) years unless revoked or cancelled by POEA due to:
    5.1 Expiration of the principal's business license;
    5.2 Cancellation of license of the local agency;
    5.3 Application for registration issues;
    5.4 Agreement issues;
    5.5 Other causes.
6. Dual Registration:
  - The Japanese principal may be registered to a maximum of two (2) Philippine licensed recruitment agencies provided that:
    6.1 The agency meets required standards;
    6.2 The principal has technical intern offer of at least 50 interns duly examined immediately preceding the registration.

