The welfare services for Overseas Filipino Workers (OFWs) which shall be transferred from the Philippine Overseas Employment Administration (POEA) to the Overseas Workers Welfare Administration (OWWA) within three months from the effectivity of the POEA Revised Rules and Regulations include the following:

1. Conciliation of complaints of workers and/or their families arising out of the following cases:
   a. Contract violations involving OFWs who are still at the jobsite;
   b. Common welfare problems outside POEA's adjudicatory or regulatory authority;
2. Request for assistance of seafarers on cases not involving POEA;
3. Repatriation of workers, remains, and transport of their belongings;
4. Airport/seaport assistance for repatriated OFWs;
5. Legal assistance to OFWs on site on cases involving employer-employee relationship;
6. Assistance in claiming unpaid allotments and in non-support cases.

